reviews.review_text: SMOKING this show just cooks from start to end.  am glad its a midwest show. the east coast shows get to crowd happy.

Memorable "Eyes" I must agree with the previous reviewer........this was a smoking show...........I remember it well but to me, this Eyes ranks up against some of the best ever.........the energy was just tremendous and with crispy Jerry throughout........the jam into Drums is flawless and amazing........If you haven't heard this Eyes, or this show, for that matter.......this is a GREAT one !!Thanks archive !

My First Dead Show And it was great! My girlfriend paid for the tickets and said if I liked it, I could pay her back. I'm not sure I did, but I should have! I was hooked, and have been ever since. It was a great show, and I could have sworn they were playing directly to my head.
What Jerry was up to before the show http://www.archive.org/details/jg1981-07-10-Interview.shnf

Hupier Paying His Girlfriend Back Hupier. While you may not of paid your girlfriend back I did. Little did you know that I was banging here at the same time as you were dating her! I gave her a 4 out of 5 just because she wouldn't swallow.

Weir's a hump post-space is legendary until Weir segues a scorching hot jam into -- Around and Around?

what a hump. 

didn't know CM was doing AUD sources now, i might have to get off my SBD snob high horse and listen to a few more.

Good Environs I know what you're saying. They might as well have ended it rather than do Around + Around. Anyway, this show was fun all around and the jam brought a huge element of surprise. Casey Jones was thoroughly enjoyed by the crowd too.
Jerry pre-show interview. Thanks for the interview tip, Revjustin.
Download this fucker Fun show with good sound. What more do you want?!

Solid Not Spectacular Yes, they played UJB and there’s a sandwich with Playing and China Doll. OK. But to me, it’s not so much what songs they played and in what order, as how they played those songs. This is certainly solid and pleasant but nothing extraordinary at all, including no long or particularly interesting jams. In short, a good but not great show. In a year with many, many truly special performances this is simply not one of them. I’d spend your time elsewhere in 1981 (e.g., 3/9/81, 5/16/81, 8/16/81, 8/28/81, 9/12/81, 11/30/81 to name just a few). Just one KatfishJohn’s opinion.
